init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Others simply do not like holding a book, and would rather listen as they go through their daily tasks.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Readers can control their pace, and so take notes on areas in the book that they may wish to look into more or take further time to understand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: While good audiobook narrators can add to the experience of a book, they are not able to replace the authors choice for the setting and other aspects

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I enjoy being able to address the story in ways that an audiobook cannot offer.
